{{World's Strongest Man Contestbox |Name =2005 World's Strongest Man |Logo =WSMLogo.jpg |Host city = {{flagicon|CHN}} [[Chengdu]], China |Nations participating =14 |Athletes participating =25 |Winner = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Mariusz Pudzianowski]] |previous = [[2004 World's Strongest Man|Nassau 2004]] |next = [[2006 World's Strongest Man|Sanya 2006]] }}
The '''2005 World's Strongest Man''' was the 28th edition of [[World's Strongest Man]] and was won by [[Mariusz Pudzianowski]] from [[Poland]]. It was his third title. [[Jesse Marunde]] from the United States finished second, and [[Dominic Filiou]] from Canada third. The contest was held at [[Chengdu]], China.<ref name=" theworldsstrongestman.com ">{{cite web |url= http://www.theworldsstrongestman.com/2005_results.php |title= theworldsstrongestman.com |accessdate=2010-01-16| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100104031924/http://theworldsstrongestman.com/2005_results.php| archivedate= 4 January 2010 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= yes}}</ref>
