{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = ICC Academy Ground | nickname = ICCA | image = | caption = | country = United Arab Emirates | location = [[Dubai Sports City]], [[Dubai]], [[United Arab Emirates]] | establishment = 2009 | seating_capacity = | international = true | firstodidate = 11 March | firstodiyear = 2013 | firstodihome = Canada | firstodiaway = Kenya | lastodidate = 23 January | lastodiyear = 2018 | lastodihome = United Arab Emirates | lastodiaway = Scotland | firstt20idate = 13 March | firstt20iyear = 2012 | firstt20ihome = Kenya | firstt20iaway = Scotland | lastt20idate = 18 December | lastt20iyear = 2016 | lastt20ihome = United Arab Emirates | lastt20iaway = Afghanistan | end1 = City End | end2 = Pavilion End | club1 = [[UAE cricket team]] | year1 = 2009-present | date = 4 March | year = 2017 | source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/India/content/ground/481147.html ESPNcricinfo }}
The '''ICC Academy Ground''' is a cricket ground located in [[Dubai Sports City]], [[Dubai]]. ICC Academy provides state-of-the-art facilities with indoor and outdoor pitches, complemented by the latest technology to allow coaches to assess all areas of a player’s game.<ref>[http://www.icc-cricket.com/about/85/icc-academy/overview ICC]</ref> ICC Academy Oval 1 has hosted a total of 18 Twenty20 matches, of which 8 have been international matches. ICC was used for the [[2014 ICC Under-19 Cricket World Cup]]. The two cricket grounds are installed with floodlights.<ref>[http://icc-cricket.yahoo.net/newsdetails.php?newsId=11746_1286893800 ICCA opens in Dubai]</ref>
==Trivia== In 2014, a match between [[Ireland cricket team|Ireland]] and [[Scotland cricket team|Scotland]] in [[Dubai Triangular Series 2014–15]] was called off. This was the first time that an [[One Day International|ODI]] in the [[UAE]] had been a no result.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/27/7457.html cricketarchive]</ref><ref>[http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/810831.html Scorecard]</ref>
