{{Infobox football biography | name = Khader Youssef | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|10|6|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Bethlehem]], [[State of Palestine|Palestine]] | height = {{convert|1.78|m|ftin|abbr=on}} | position = [[Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[Tarji Wadi Al-Nes|Wadi Al-Nes]] | clubnumber = 10 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Tarji Wadi Al-Nes|Wadi Al-Nes]] | years1 = 2004– | clubs1 = [[Tarji Wadi Al-Nes|Wadi Al-Nes]] | caps1= 167 | goals1= 10 | years2 = 2013 | clubs2= → [[Al-Faisaly FC (Amman)|Al-Faisaly]] (loan) | caps2= 7| goals2= 2 | nationalyears1 = 2008– | nationalteam1 = [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]] | nationalcaps1 = 68 | nationalgoals1 = 2 | club-update =6 June 2014 | nationalteam-update = 20 November 2017 }}
'''Khader Yousef Abu Hammad''' ({{lang-ar|خضر يوسف}}; born 6 October 1984) is a [[Palestinian people|Palestinian]] [[association football|footballer]] playing for [[Tarji Wadi Al-Nes]] of the [[West Bank Premier League]] as a [[midfielder]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kooora.com/?player=30971 |language=Arabic |title=Khader Yousef – Player profile |accessdate=8 December 2011 |work=kooora.com}}</ref>
He received his first national team cap for [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]] in 2008 against Jordan in the first FIFA-sanctioned match held in Palestine since the 1930s. He has since played for Palestine at the [[2010 West Asian Football Federation Championship]], the qualifying rounds of the [[2010 AFC Challenge Cup qualification|2010 Challenge Cup]], [[2012 AFC Challenge Cup qualification|2012 AFC Challenge Cup]], and in [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2014 World Cup qualifying]].
