{{Korean name|Ku}} {{Infobox boxer | name = Ku Yong-jo | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | weight = | height = <!-- "X ft Y in" or "X cm" (conversions are automatic) --> | reach = <!-- "X in" or "X cm" (conversions are automatic) --> | nationality = | birth_date = July 17, 1955 | birth_place = | death_date = {{death-date and age|March 2001|July 17, 1955}} | death_place = | style = | total = | wins = | KO = | losses = | draws = | no contests = | website = | medaltemplates = {{MedalSport | Men's [[Boxing at the Summer Olympics|boxing]]}} {{MedalCountry | {{PRK}} }} {{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}} {{MedalGold| [[1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Montreal]] | [[Boxing at the 1976 Summer Olympics|Bantamweight]]}} | show-medals = | embed = <!-- "yes" allows infobox embedding --> }} {{Infobox Korean name | hangul = 구영조 | hanja = | rr = Gu Yeong-jo | mr = Ku Yŏng-jo | context = north }}
'''Ku Yong-jo''' (July 17, 1955 – March 2001) was a [[boxing|boxer]] from [[North Korea]], who won the gold medal in the [[bantamweight]] (&ndash;54&nbsp;kg) division at the [[Boxing at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Summer Olympics]] in [[Montreal, Quebec]], Canada. In the final, he defeated American boxer [[Charles Mooney]].<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=DPRK Sportspersons Prove Successful at Olympic Games |url=http://www.kcna.co.jp/item/2012/201208/news02/20120802-29ee.html |newspaper= |location= |publisher=[[Korean Central News Agency]] |date=August 2, 2012 |accessdate= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812205641/http://www.kcna.co.jp/item/2012/201208/news02/20120802-29ee.html |archivedate=August 12, 2014 |df= }}</ref> In 1980, he competed in the [[featherweight]] division and, after receiving a first-round bye, lost his first bout to [[Krzysztof Kosedowski]] of Poland.
== Olympic results == '''Montreal 1976'''
*1st round bye * Round of 32: Defeated [[Faredin Ibrahim]] (Romania) on points, 4–1 * Round of 16: Defeated [[Chacho Andreykovski]] (Bulgaria) on points, 5–0 * Quarterfinal: Defeated [[Weerachart Saturngrun]] (Thailand) on points, 5–0 * Semifinal: Defeated [[Pat Cowdell]] (Great Britain) on points, 4–1 * Final: Defeated [[Charles Mooney]] (United States) on points, 5–0 (won gold medal)
'''Moscow 1980'''
