{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name =Pocheon Stadium | image = | location = [[Pocheon]], [[Gyeonggi Province]], [[South Korea]] | broke_ground = | opened = 1990 | owner = City of Pocheon | operator = City of Pocheon | surface = Artificial grass | tenants = [[FC Pocheon]] | seating_capacity = 5,964 }}
'''Pocheon Stadium''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Pocheon]], [[South Korea]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches. The stadium has a capacity of 5,964 seats and was opened in 1990. It was home ground of [[FC Pocheon]].
