'''Stade St. Claude''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Basse-Terre]], [[Guadeloupe]]. The stadium is home to the [[Guadeloupe national football team]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches. The stadium holds 10,000. It is currently used by football teams [[Racing Club de Basse-Terre]] and [[La Gauloise de Basse-Terre]]. <ref>http://www.worldstadiums.com/middle_america/countries/guadeloupe.shtml "World Stadiums  - Guadeloupe" Retrieved 16 August 2011 </ref>

